Spain was expected to relax its rules this week, but it extended them until the end of April. Britons must fill out a Health Control Form and a jab must have been given to a sun-seeker within the last 270 days - but teenagers do not need to be vaccinated.   Officials hope this year's international arrivals will reach 80 percent of pre-Covid levels - and noted that "uncertainty" caused by Russia's invasion does not seem to have deterred travellers.